```
UNITED STATES DISTRICT COURT
FOR THE EASTERN DISTRICT OF PENNSYLVANIA

CARD CONNECT, LLC,

Plaintiff,
v.

SHIFT4 PAYMENTS, LLC, et al.,

Defendants.

CIVIL ACTION
NO. 2:17-cv-05162-BMS

                                                ORDER

      AND NOW, this 6th day of October 2020, upon consideration of Defendants' Motion
for Partial Summary Judgment (ECF No. 127) and Plaintiff's Response thereto (ECF No. 137),
and Defendants' Motion to Seal (ECF No. 128), it is hereby ORDERED that:
1.  Defendants' Motion for Partial Summary Judgment is GRANTED IN PART AND
DENIED IN PART. Specifically:

      a.   Summary Judgment is GRANTED as to Count I on the issue of whether the
           development of a competing product, without more, constitutes a breach of the implied
          covenant of good faith and fair dealing.

      b. Summary Judgment is GRANTED as to Count IV.

     c. Summary Judgment is DENIED as to the remaining issues in Count I.
2. Defendants' Motion to Seal is GRANTED.
      IT IS SO ORDERED.

                                                     By:/s/ Berle M. Schiller
                                                     BERLE M. SCHILLER, J.
```
